about.summary: Provides a 'tbl_ts' class (the 'tsibble') to store and manage temporal data in a data-centric format, which is built on top of the 'tibble'. The 'tsibble' aims at easily manipulating and analysing temporal data, including counting and filling in time gaps, aggregate over calendar periods, performing rolling window calculations, and etc.

name: r-tsibble
raw_recipe:
{% set version = '0.8.2' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-tsibble
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/tsibble_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/tsibble/tsibble_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: a310dda724096a17680165c75f9bf4f205ba03708535a7e0611f11e0628d32b6

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}              # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}            # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_cxx') }}      # [win]
    - {{posix}}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{posix}}make
    - {{posix}}sed               # [win]
    - {{posix}}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{posix}}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-rcpp >=0.12.3
    - r-anytime >=0.3.1
    - r-dplyr >=0.8.0
    - r-lubridate >=1.7.0
    - r-purrr >=0.2.3
    - r-rlang >=0.2.0
    - r-tibble >=2.0.1
    - r-tidyr
    - r-tidyselect
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{native}}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-rcpp >=0.12.3
    - r-anytime >=0.3.1
    - r-dplyr >=0.8.0
    - r-lubridate >=1.7.0
    - r-purrr >=0.2.3
    - r-rlang >=0.2.0
    - r-tibble >=2.0.1
    - r-tidyr
    - r-tidyselect

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('tsibble')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('tsibble')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://tsibble.tidyverts.org
  license: GPL-3
  summary: Provides a 'tbl_ts' class (the 'tsibble') to store and manage temporal data in a data-centric
    format, which is built on top of the 'tibble'. The 'tsibble' aims at easily manipulating
    and analysing temporal data, including counting and filling in time gaps, aggregate
    over calendar periods, performing rolling window calculations, and etc.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - philip-khor
